Question: Should the government provide free college education to everyone the same way it provides high school education? Explain your answer.
Answer:
 According to me the government should provide free college education because it's in the natural continuity of high school, people cannot work just right after high school, that is why they need college education. Given the fact that college education improves the development and the well-being of a society, free college education should be considered as a retributing investment. 